#Text=Ingrid Newkirk on Ingrid Newkirk
#Text=DS :
#Text=Did you and Alex Pacheco have a falling out ?
#Text=IN : No — well , we ’ve had many fallings out in our years —
#Text=DS : Like a family —
#Text=IN : Yes , yes .
#Text=We ’ve had many an argument , many a falling out , but he separated a long time ago .
#Text=DS : Are you still in contact with him ?
#Text=IN : Yes , he was in touch with the office a couple of weeks ago .
#Text=I was on the road .
#Text=DS : Is he looking at becoming involved again ?
#Text=IN : I ’m not sure what he wants to do at the moment and I ’m not sure he does , either .
#Text=DS : How would Ingrid Newkirk twenty years ago look at Ingrid Newkirk now ?
#Text=IN : God , what a horrid question ! [ Laughs ]
#Text=Do you mean twenty years ago ?
#Text=Because we ’ve had the group twenty-seven years .
#Text=DS : Just twenty years ago , the person you were then looking at the person you are now .
#Text=IN : God , less wrinkles ! I do n’t know the answer to that .
#Text=I really do n’t .
#Text=DS : Do you think you ’ve achieved a lot of the things you had wanted back then ?
#Text=IN : I ’m never looking ahead .
#Text=All I want is to reduce suffering and to get people to think of animals in a different way , and that ’s as true then as it is now .
#Text=Perhaps I was — I do n’t know if I could say if I ’m less or more optimistic , I really ca n’t .
#Text=I think I was just me , only younger .
#Text=DS : Do you think other people would say that ?
#Text=IN : I think so…I think so .
#Text=I do n’t know , really .
#Text=DS : Do you have any regrets ?
#Text=IN : Professionally ?
#Text=Because that ’s what we are talking about …
#Text=DS : Or personally .
#Text=IN : I ’m not going to talk about personally !
#Text=DS : Just in general — in your life .
#Text=IN :

#Text=These are just terrible questions ! I think you can always look back and in hindsight , knowing the results of what you ’ve done , think , ‘ Maybe I could have been more strategic then ’ ; or ‘ If I had only known…maybe I could have pushed harder then . ’

#Text=But I think in compromising sometimes , people may find it surprising , but I ’m so anxious not to lose ground , but to gain ground so that we can move ahead , that I might take less than if I had known I could have pushed harder what I could have got .
#Text=DS : See .
#Text=Sometimes terrible questions birth wonderful answers .
#Text=IN : Oh , pwah !
#Text=DS : The nature of this interview is on a permanent encyclopedia —
#Text=IN : Ah ! God , help me , kill me .
#Text=DS : -- so the questions are designed not just around your work , but also around who you are as a person .
